Click "File → New → Dynamic Web Project"
Enter Project Name as "Practical7"
Select "Apache Tomcat v9.0" in Target Runtime
Click "Next"
Click "Next"
Click "Finish"

Expand "Practical7 → Java Resources → src/main/java"
Right click "src/main/java"
Click "New → Servlet"
Enter Class Name as "HelloServlet"
Click "Finish"
Delete generated code
Paste HelloServlet.java code
Press "Ctrl + S"

Expand "src → main → webapp"
Right click "webapp"
Click "New → HTML File"
Enter File Name as "input.html"
Click "Finish"
Delete generated HTML code
Paste HTML code
Press "Ctrl + S"

Open "Window → Show View → Servers"
Click "Create a new server"
Select "Apache Tomcat v9.0 Server"
Click "Next"
Select "Practical7"
Click "Add >"
Click "Finish"

In Servers tab, right click "Tomcat v9.0 Server at localhost"
Click "Start"
Wait for message "Started, Synchronized"
Right click "input.html"
Click "Run As → Run on Server"
Select "Tomcat v9.0"
Click "Finish"

Browser opens automatically
Enter Username and Password
Click "Login"
Output displays entered Username and Password
